import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    series = data['Series'].unique()
    colors = ['red', 'green', 'blue', 'orange']
    for i, s in enumerate(series):
        df = data[data['Series'] == s]
        ax.scatter(df['X'], df['Y'], color=colors[i], label=s)
        ax.legend()
    plt.title('What is the correlation between X and Y for each series?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    series = data.groupby('Series')
    x_mean = series['X'].mean()
    x_std = series['X'].std()
    ax.bar(x_mean.index, x_mean.values, yerr=x_std.values, capsize=10)
    ax.set_title('What is the mean and standard deviation of X for each series?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, axs = plt.subplots(2, 2, figsize=(10, 10))
    axs = axs.flatten()
    for i, series in enumerate(data['Series'].unique()):
        axs[i].hist(data[data['Series'] == series]['Y'], bins=10, alpha=0.5, label=series)
        axs[i].set_title(f'Distribution of Y for {series}')
        axs[i].legend()
    fig.suptitle('What is the distribution of Y for each series?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
